FBIS3-19801 "drweu056__a94015" FBIS-WEU-94-056-A Document Type:Daily Report 23 March 1994 ANNEX Germany Bundeswehr General Huber Offers To Resign AU1803173594 Hamburg DPA in German 1415 GMT 18 Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU1803173594 Hamburg DPA Language: German Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Bonn -- The special representative for rationalization measures within the Bundeswehr, General Lorenz Huber, has asked for his dismissal. The Defense Ministry confirmed the step of the 57-year-old general today. As DPA learned, he cited lacking support for his proposed austerity measures by senior generals as the reason for his departure. The Defense Ministry announced that no decision has yet been made regarding Huber's request. The defense expert of the Christian Democratic Union, Paul Breuer, demanded the "unconditional examination of all of Huber's proposals and a clarification of the circumstances that prompted Huber to take this personal step." Juergen Koppelin from the Free Democratic Party of Germany spoke of a "serious warning" for Defense Minister Volker Ruehe (Christian Democratic Union). [passage omitted]
